Usage: add_gui_shape [-help] [-layer <layerName>] [-name <guiShapeName>]
                     [-width <width>] {-rect {x1 y1 x2 y2} | -line {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...} | -polygon {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...}} [ -line {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...} [-arrow ] ]

-help                       # Prints out the command usage
-arrow                      # Draw arrow in the middle of the line with
                            # direction from start point to end point
                            # (bool, required)
-layer <layerName>          # GUI layer name to use or create for the
                            # rect/line. If the specified layer does not exist,
                            # it will be automatically created the name as
                            # guiShapeLayer. (string, optional)
-line {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...}     # The beginning and ending coordinates for the line
                            # segments (values are in microns)
                            # (point_list, optional)
-name <guiShapeName>        # The name of the GUI shape (string, optional)
-polygon {x1 y1 x2 y2 ...}  # The coordinates for the polygon segment (values
                            # are in microns) (point_list, optional)
-rect {x1 y1 x2 y2}         # Coordinates of the lower-left and upper-right
                            # points of the rectangle (values are in microns)
                            # (box, optional)
-width <width>              # Number of pixels in the border of the object
                            # (int, optional, min=1, max=7)